1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) - The paper discusses the use of Winograd convolution algorithms, which are commonly used in computer vision tasks such as image classification and object detection. 
2. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) - The paper discusses the use of quantized neural networks and proposes optimizations to improve their efficiency, which falls under the scope of neural and evolutionary computing. 
3. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper proposes a new class of Winograd algorithms and discusses optimizations to reduce the number of general multiplications, which are related to data structures and algorithms. 
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper discusses the use of deep neural networks and proposes optimizations to improve their efficiency, which falls under the scope of machine learning. 
5. cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) - The paper discusses the challenges of implementing and executing Winograd algorithms on hardware accelerators, which falls under the scope of hardware architecture.
